text: Chionodes manabiensis is a moth in the family Gelechiidae. It is found in Ecuador.Chionodes at funet The wingspan is 9–10 mm for males and 9.5-11.9 mm for females. ==Etymology== The species name is derived from Manabí, Ecuador, the type locality.Rev. suisse zool. 114 : 180 ==References== Category:Chionodes Category:Moths described in 2007 Category:Moths of South America
title: Chionodes manabiensis
